ENGR. H. B. NO. 4280 Page 5

1 D. The Department of Transportation shall use the monies in the
2 Rebuilding Oklahoma Access and Driver Safety Fund for:
3 1. The construction and maintenance of state roads, bridges and
4 highways;
5 2. The direct expenses of operating and maintaining the state
6 highway system, including bridges;
7 3. Direct expenses incurred in constructing, repairing, and
8 maintaining state highways, farm-to-market roads, county highways
9 and bridges as authorized by law;
10 4. Matching federal funds;
11 5. The purchase of materials, tools, machinery, motor vehicles,
12 and equipment necessary or convenient for the construction and
13 maintenance of the state highway system and bridges;
14 6. Debt service incurred prior to January 1, 2006, for Capital
15 Improvement Program bonds sold pursuant to Section 2001 of this
16 title;
17 7. Debt service incurred on or after July 1, 2009, with respect
18 to obligations authorized to be issued pursuant to Section 341 151
19 et seq. of Title 73 of the Oklahoma Statutes, Section 350 of Title
20 73 of the Oklahoma Statutes and Section 1 of Enrolled House Bill No.
21 2896 of the 1st Session of the 58th Oklahoma Legislature; and
22 8. For fiscal years beginning on or after July 1, 2025, and
23 ending on or prior to June 30, 2033, Twenty Million Dollars
24
ENGR. H. B. NO. 4280 Page 6

1 ($20 ,000,000.00) per fiscal year for the construction, repair, and
2 maintenance of weigh stations on the state highway system.
3 E. From the monies allocated pursuant to the provisions of
4 subparagraph a of paragraph 1 of subsection B of this section each
5 fiscal year, the Department of Transportation shall make payments
6 required for the payment of principal, interest and other costs
7 related to the obligations issued by the Oklahoma Capitol
8 Improvement Authority as authorized by Section 341 of Title 73 of
9 the Oklahoma Statutes, Section 350 of Title 73 of the Oklahoma
10 Statutes and Section 1 of Enrolled House Bill No. 2896 of the 1st
11 Session of the 58th Oklahoma Legislature, and such payments shall be
12 made by the Department each fiscal year before such monies are used
13 for any other purpose.
14 F. In the event that the Department of Transportation must
15 delay projects or remove projects from its Eight-Year Construction
16 Work Plan outside its normal adjustments, it shall notify in writing
17 the Governor, the Speaker of the Oklahoma House of Representatives,
18 the President Pro Tempore of the Oklahoma State Senate, the
19 Appropriations and Budget Chair of the Oklahoma House of
20 Representatives, and the Appropriations Chair of the Oklahoma State
21 Senate, and both the House member and Senate member whose district
22 the project resides in. A copy of such notice shall be on file at
23 the ODOT District Office overseeing the project. The notice shall
24 include:
ENGR. H. B. NO. 4280 Page 7

1 1. A project description detailing the original project and
2 what is being adjusted or removed;
3 2. An explanation of why the adjustment or removal is being
4 made;
5 3. The amount of funding needed to keep the project in its
6 original scope and timeline; and
7 4. How this change affects the Asset Preservation Plan.
8 Such notice shall be provided within one (1) week of the
9 Transportation Commission's meeting approving the updated Eight-Year
10 Construction Work Plan, where such delays or removals are approved.
11 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
12 Passed the House of Representatives the 11th day of March, 2026.
